b'' b'[please accept the following announcement for comp.windows.x.announce. -gf]' b'' b'a completely revamped version of the x11 browser interface to archie,' b'xarchie, is now available as' b'export.lcs.mit.edu:/contrib/xarchie-2.0.tar.z' b'' b'for those not familar with archie or xarchie, i include part of the' b'manpage intro:' b'' b'xarchie is an x11 browser interface to the archie internet information' b'system using the prospero virtual filesystem protocol. archie' b'provides information about files available for ftp anywhere on the' b'internet; xarchie displays this information using an easy-to-use,' b'point-and-click interface. xarchie allows you to further explore ftp' b'sites by examining directories returned as query matches, and allows' b'you to retrieve files located this way.' b'' b'xarchie has been extensively tested on r4, r5, and a variety of' b'other flavors of x, and on a wide range of machines. a summary of the' b'new features (from the readme) follows:' b'' b'* major improvements include:' b'- multiple selections allowed in browser for use with other new' b'features (fwf multilist widget).' b'- ability to expand directories in browser.' b'- real fully-integrated ftp implementation.' b'- ability to save and reload query results, as well as print them.' b'- ability to resort results, and sort results by user-definable' b'pseudo-weights.' b'- online help browser.' b"- color resources, done so that they don't break mono displays." b'- fwf fileselector widget for local file operations.' b"- makefile.dst's supplied for the imake-impaired." b'' b'george' b'--' b'dept. of computer science uucp: rutgers!rochester!ferguson' b'university of rochester vox: b'rochester ny fax: 